  id: Cervical_part_of_trapezius_muscle.R
  partName: Cervical part of trapezius muscle Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right cervical part of the trapezius muscle occupies the upper neck and shoulder
    region of the canine body and assists in scapular movement. Originating from
    the cervical midline and inserting onto the scapular spine, it functions to elevate
    and draw the scapula cranially during limb advancement.
  - This muscle contributes significantly to posture, shoulder stabilization, and
    smooth forelimb motion during locomotion. Working with surrounding musculature,
    it supports coordinated limb mechanics and balanced movement patterns. The cervical
    trapezius is especially active during activities requiring rapid directional
    adjustments or climbing.
